<br>
This is what worked for me...<br>
<br>
SolA - I was about 52 when I soloed him.  Hard part is getting there and clearing.  Be prepared for a long camp.  Mine was about 19 hours (57 spawns I think).  I got friends to come in with me (1 melee about your level and you is enough to clear.  You can probably do it yourself in a pinch, but, easy with a good tank)  As part of the clearing to get there, stagger the pops in the room so you will be taking them on one at a time.  I camped in the E corner of the room next to Gimblox so I could see into room, but, not get aggro - camp just north enough to see both pops, but, not too far north cause you might get aggro from room to the north.  Go into the Gimblox room to fight when they pop so that you don't get aggro/adds from the room directly north of where you are watching from.  I do not know about TLC for Gimblox.  I have heard it is not a problem, but, after 19 hours, I was taking NO chances.  I shouted for help when he popped and a couple people I had been buffing/healing swung by to kill him for me, refused payment, and went back to doing their thing afterwards. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->      Something else I did at one point was brought 2 34ish friends along and healed/buffed them while they had a grand old time terrorizing that area of SolA.  There is some pretty good loot/exp for that level there and if you have a rogue, they can sell to goblin merchant nearby.  (Also reduces boredom factor if you have friends along).<br>
<br>
Aqua goblins I also did about at your level.  I had a L52 rogue and myself and he was easy.  You can solo him, but, if a couple things go wrong on you, you might get into trouble.  (My theory on epics is to take no chances.)  I pacified two around him (or PH) and pulled to the nearby island and fought it out there.  I put celestial on myself and nuked at extreme range to pull him - he will nuke you back.  Other people I know fight in water, but, I thought that was a pain and didn't bother.  Do NOT aggro deep or whatever the name of the red con is...  Bergurgle is not a green at your level, so no TLC issues.<br>
<br>
Also, get started on fragments if you ever have somebody to group with - avoid chromodracs cause they have debuffs.  Just pull the weaker stuff if possible.  Drakes are immune to stuns.  I also did shouts/auctions for looting rights - think I got one or two that way in addition to what my group killed.<br>
<br>
I have seen you on a couple raids already, there are a lot of people willing to help that you have probably met in the few raids you have already been on.  I had the same problem, I am kinda shy and not good at getting 20 plus people to help me...lol...  However, although I am not there yet, I am pretty sure at this point I have enough friends/people I have helped on epics that my time will come.  You are a very friendly, like-able person and although it is intimidating to ask for help, you will succeed at it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Hope this helps.  Send me a tell if I am on and I will be more than happy to give advice/help if you need it.<br>
<br>
