<br>
On Bergugle, I was lucky  I always checked him when I went to my guilds arena events, and one time he was up. I've ended up finding him 3 time for various clerics and camping him for 2 more. The  tower is simple you can level pull burgugles place holder at 54 ( perhaps lower ). I've duo'd him with a 54 sk / cleric and done he's pretty easy with fear or stun I've the cleric nukes with knock back make him a bit of a pain to fight under water but he's still doable there.<br>
( His crown is droppable, so you might be able to find one for sale, or have your friends pick one up )<br>
<br>
The last thing a low 50 cleric can do in a group is get to skyfire and get your shards, this can likely be the most frustrateing part of the quest. Keep a group there, and keep auctioning / shouting/ telling anyone else in zone that you're looking for the shards, most times there are just folks soloing there for spells so the shard is useless , no drop, and not multiquestable ( well sorta again this depends on how much you trust the person )<br>
<br>
After that it's more of a guild thing as to weither or not you get your epic, or a huge level thing and you can do most of it single grouped.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rundonundodundo>Rundo Nundodundo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ghetto Cleric</span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/16/03 9:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> shards</span><hr size=1> Ok yeah you can solo Gimblox and Begurgle for the start.  May need help depending on your equip/level.  However, i wouldn't seriously consider getting epic unless you have the 4 shards from skyfire mountains.  These are extremely rare and hard to get and once you have all 4 then i believe you are ready to go go go for you epic.  Odds of finding shards are 1 in a 100 off of any mobs in Skyfire don't let anyone tell you different... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sulissaurnvelve>Sulissa UrnVelve</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/17/03 11:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: shards</span><hr size=1> They're not to bad if you hold the area around the entrance of VP ..<br>
