<br>
If you can, DO IT WHILE IT'S XP.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Seriously, it's far more demoralizing when it's all 95% green, 4% light blue and 1% dark blue, and your AA XP bar moves 2% in like 5 hours.  Don't put it off if it's not too late.<br>
<br>
King in Chardok - this part (the singed scroll) is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>droppable</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> on FV.  I actually have an extra one, and I'm debating what to do with it.  Might sell, might find a deserving person who can't get guild support, who knows.<br>
<br>
No part of this quest is so hard a single group can't do it at the right levels.  So, if you are having a hard time getting people to help you, my advice is level up, and come back to it later.  Chardok is duoable at 60+ with faction (killing in droga a LOT) for an enchanter and cleric, but you have to protect the pet from having charm dispelled by the king's AE (junk buffs, can be tricky) and use pacify to get a clean pull.  Plus you have to clear 5 roamers in the hall first.  Without faction, I'm pretty confident a full group of 60+ can do it just fine, if you pull carefully on your way (pacify everything).<br>
<br>
I wrote a guide because all the guides I saw out there were either out of date or low quality or both.  Another thing I hated about the guides is they numbers of people they said were needed (mostly from being written in the Kunark era).  It might be of use, especially to people who want to do the cleric epic without huge raids.<br>
